PHP Variables 
As the algebra, PHP variables cab=n be used to hold values or expressions. 
Rules: 
•	Variable starts with $ sign 
•	It followed by the name of the variable
•	Variable name must start with a letter or the underscore character, but not a number
•	Variable names are case sensitive.
Ex: 
<html>
<body>
<h1>PHP Variables</h1>
<?php
$x=5; // assign value to variable
$y=6; // assign value to variable
$z=$x+$y;
echo "<h3>Z=".$z."</h3>";
?>
</body>
</html>
PHP Data Types
String 				Integer 		Float 			Boolean 
Array 				Object 			Null
